10.14.21  11:01 pm   What happens if I have a really good idea for a chorus and no verse to go with it? If the chorus is the best part of the song (in many cases), why aren't songs just choruses over and over again?

     sometimes they are. the only way to know if this works for your song is to try it

     If verses are used to separate chorus from chorus, why don't we make verses exactly like choruses, and make songs that switch back and forth between two different equally catchy choruses?

      you can try anything you want and see what you like best. but, think of it like drawing hills. try to draw a bunch of hills but only the high part. make them stay high the entire time. hopefully this may help you understand the game we're dealing with
